<html>
  <problem>
    <title> More than one Pulley </title>
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="11"/>
    <p>In the diagram, the pulleys and the strings are massless. The strings do not stretch. The masses of the suspended blocks are \(m_1\) and \(m_2\), as shown. The magnitudes of the accelerations of the blocks are \(a_1\) and \(a_2\), respectively.</p><br/><img encrypturl="no" src="/static/problems/MIT/rayyan/check_points/BK/BK26.png" alt="p1a" texwrap="none" align="top"/><br/><u><b>Part1:</b></u> What is the correct relationship between \(a_1\) and \(a_2\)?

    <part loncapaid="15">
      <br/>
      <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" randomize="yes" loncapaid="12" type="MultipleChoice">
        <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
          <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                 \(a_1\) = \(a_2\)
            
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="true">

                 \(2a_1\) = \(a_2\)
            
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                 \(a_1\) = \(2a_2\)
            
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">

                 (\(\frac{m_1}{m_2}\))\(a_1\) = \(a_2\)
            
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">

                 (\(\frac{m_2}{m_1}\))\(a_1\) = \(a_2\)
            
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">

                 (\(\frac{m_1}{m_2}\))\(a_1\) = \(2a_2\)
            
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>
    </part>
    <br/>
    
      <p><u><b>Part2:</b></u> What must be the relationship between the masses of the blocks so that the blocks would be in equilibrium?
</p>
    
    <part loncapaid="16">
      <br/>
      <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" randomize="yes" loncapaid="14" type="MultipleChoice">
        <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
          <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                 \(m_1\) = \(m_2\)
            
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">

                 \(2m_1\) = \(m_2\)
            
          </choice>
          <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="true">

                 \(m_1\) = \(2m_2\)
            
          </choice>
          <choice location="bottom" name="foil4" correct="false">

                 The blocks cannot be in equilibrium, no matter what the ration of masses is
            
          </choice>
        </choicegroup>
      </multiplechoiceresponse>
    </part>
      </problem>
</html>
